    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    In this letter, <persName>Aline Burch</persName> writes on behalf of her company <orgName>the Hogarth Press <choice><abbr>Ltd.</abbr><expan>Limited</expan></choice></orgName> to 
                    <persName><choice><abbr>Dr.</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Friedich Michael</persName>, who works for the publisher <orgName>Insel Verlag</orgName>. Aline tells <choice><abbr>Dr.</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Michael 
                that she has enclosed a copy of the novel SADO by <persName>William Plomer</persName>. She thinks he will 
                greatly enjoy the authorâ€™s work, but also thinks that he might be interested in 
                translating said novel to German. She also mentions that the initial request comes from
                    <persName><choice><abbr>Dr.</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> L.L. Weltmann</persName>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1951-10-12">
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <persName><choice><abbr>Dr.</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Friedich Michael</persName>
                            <lb/><orgName>Insel-Verlag</orgName>, 
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine> Karlstrasse 38, 
                        <lb/><placeName><choice><sic>Weisbaden</sic><corr>Wiesbaden</corr></choice></placeName>, Germany. 
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <seg>
                        <persName><choice><abbr>AB</abbr><expan>Aline Burch</expan></choice></persName>    
                    </seg>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName key="Q1461148"><choice><abbr>Dr.</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Michael</persName>, 
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <lb/>   We have been asked by <persName key="Q55675211"><choice><abbr>Dr.</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> L.L.
                   <lb/>   Weltmann</persName> to let you have a copy of 
                    <lb/>   SADO by <persName key="Q1282985">William Plomer</persName> and I have 
                    <lb/>   pleasure in enclosing a copy.   <choice><abbr>Dr.</abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> 
                   <lb/>   <persName>Weltmann</persName> thinks that you would like
                   <lb/>   to consider this book with a view to 
                   <lb/>   a German translation and that you might
                   <lb/>   probably be interested in <persName><choice><abbr>Mr.</abbr><expan>Mister</expan></choice> Plomer's</persName>
                   <lb/>   work as a whole.    We very much hope 
                   <lb/>   that you will be impressed by SADO 
                   <lb/>   and shall look forward to hearing 
                   <lb/>   from you about it in due course. 
                   
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        Yours sincerely, 
                        <lb/>for <orgName key="Q1623362">the Hogarth Press <choice><abbr>Ltd.</abbr><expan>Limited</expan></choice></orgName>
                    </salute>
                    <signed/>
                    <seg>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div>
